			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Started digging into the circuitry a bit, and it looks like the 2A03 handles <strong>rdy</strong> for OAM DMA and PCM reads in a pretty clever way. Rather than just pulling <strong>rdy</strong> low for a fixed safe &quot;minimum&quot; time, it first pulls it low and then waits for a CPU read. Once it sees a read, it knows <strong>rdy</strong> must have kicked in, and moves on to doing the transfer.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
